-- Sears Holdings Plans to Close as Many as 120 Kmart, Sears Full-Line Stores
-- B y   S t e v e n   F r o m m
-- 2011-12-27T11:06:08Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-12-27/sears-holdings-plans-to-close-as-many-as-120-kmart-sears-full-line-stores.html
Sears Holdings Corp. (SHLD)  said it will
close 100 to 120 Kmart and Sears Full-line stores.  Sears said it also expects to record in the fourth quarter
a non-cash charge related to a valuation allowance on certain
deferred tax assets of $1.6 to $1.8 billion.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Steven Fromm at 
 sfromm@bloomberg.net  